<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-05-18T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-05-18T10:00:00-05:00" n="812" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d812">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/64: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-18T09:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">May 18,
                                        1921—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:10
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>24. President Meléndez informs me that he is negotiating a loan of
                            $10,000,000 through Bloom Brothers, an American firm New York, to be
                            guaranteed by a percentage of the customhouse receipts. The lenders will
                            appoint a controller of the customhouses of the Republic.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Arnold</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>